RTF Control - Access Granted
It is a code within Rich Text Format manipulated by hackers to embed malicious code or exploit vulnerabilities when parsing the file.
Embed the OLE objects (Object Linking and Embedding)
Mitigations: disable auto-exec of OLE objects, use secure email gateways, update for latest security patches.

Ransomware Task Force (RTF)

Honeypot - a decoy system used to lure cybercriminals into attacking a fake target (isolated from the network).
used to gather information about the hackers' techniques and motivations.
Within the network, Near high-value subnets, Within IoT networks, and In cloud environments.
used for detect and analyze intrusions, diverting attackers to a less critical systems, organizations understand how attackers are exploiting IoT devices.
